Locked architectural decisions
1. Execution is independent of the Decision

The Decision determines whether execution is authorized.

The Execution records what actually happened.

2. Execution lifecycle is authoritative

Execution state is represented only by:

PROCESSING
COMPLETED
FAILED

There is no separate outcome field.

3. Multiple Executions are supported

A Business Transaction may have:

zero Executions
one Execution
multiple Executions

Each Execution has its own:

executionId
lifecycle
evidence
timestamps
4. Evidence belongs to the Execution

Evidence is generated during execution and is permanently associated with that specific Execution.

Examples include:

external transaction reference
API response
execution logs
downstream acknowledgment
execution hash
5. Execution is immutable

Once an Execution reaches a terminal state:

COMPLETED
FAILED

it cannot be modified.

Any subsequent attempt is recorded as a new Execution, preserving the append-only history defined by the Execution Trust Model.

Canonical Principle (Locked)

Execution records what happened after authorization.

It is an immutable trust artifact that captures execution state, timestamps, and evidence without altering the original Decision or Business Transaction.

{
  "$schema": "https://json-schema.org/draft/2020-12/schema",
  "$id": "https://schemas.parmana.ai/common/execution.schema.json",
  "title": "Execution",
  "description": "Canonical Execution artifact for a Business Transaction.",
  "type": "object",
  "additionalProperties": false,
  "required": [
    "executionId",
    "status",
    "startedAt"
  ],
  "properties": {
    "executionId": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Unique Execution identifier."
    },
    "status": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Execution lifecycle state.",
      "enum": [
        "PROCESSING",
        "COMPLETED",
        "FAILED"
      ]
    },
    "mode": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Execution mode.",
      "enum": [
        "SYNC",
        "ASYNC"
      ]
    },
    "startedAt": {
      "type": "string",
      "format": "date-time",
      "description": "UTC timestamp when execution started."
    },
    "completedAt": {
      "type": "string",
      "format": "date-time",
      "description": "UTC timestamp when execution completed."
    },
    "evidence": {
      "type": "object",
      "description": "Execution evidence captured during execution.",
      "additionalProperties": true
    },
    "metadata": {
      "type": "object",
      "description": "Execution-specific metadata.",
      "additionalProperties": true
    }
  },
  "examples": [
    {
      "executionId": "EXEC-000001",
      "status": "COMPLETED",
      "mode": "SYNC",
      "startedAt": "2026-06-26T10:30:00Z",
      "completedAt": "2026-06-26T10:30:02Z",
      "evidence": {
        "targetSystem": "Payment Gateway",
        "referenceId": "PG-987654321"
      },
      "metadata": {
        "executor": "payment-service"
      }
    }
  ]
}